article.title: Quark Seesaw, Dark $U(1)$ symmetry and Baryon-Dark Matter Coincidence

multiple_choice_question.text: What does the matrix element YF*UR/MF represent in the context of this mass matrix?
choices: The Yukawa coupling between the [SU(2)]-doublet and singlet fermions.
The VEV of the [SU(2)R]-doublet Higgs scalar.

multiple_choice_question.text: What is the significance of the mixing angles θL and θR in the context of dark matter?
choices: They determine the strength of the interaction between dark matter and the Higgs boson.
They control the decay rate of dark matter into neutrinos and dark gauge bosons.
They govern the annihilation rate of dark matter into dark photons.
They dictate the mass splitting between the dark matter particle and its antiparticle.

multiple_choice_question.text: What is the primary factor determining the efficiency of dark matter annihilation in this scenario?
choices: The mass of the dark photon (mX).
The mass of the dark matter particle (mx).
The VEV of the light dark scalar (vξ).

multiple_choice_question.text: Which parameter in this formula is directly constrained by experiments looking for dark matter-proton scattering?
choices: The mass of the dark photon (mX).
The kinetic mixing parameter between U(1)B-L and U(1)x (ε).
The mass of the dark matter particle (mx).
